&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cards team at Stripe is responsible for the infrastructure, user facing features, and business of accepting credit, debit, and pre-paid card payments. Delivering the best offering for processing credit, debit, and prepaid cards is critical to Stripe’s mission, given the central role card payments play in internet commerce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a product manager to drive our Stripe Cards Vault product efforts and strategy globally. Specifically, this product manager will own a critical card payments performance product that is used by millions of Stripe customers to tokenize, manage and update their card credentials. Our Cards Vault is paramount to our customers as it directly helps grow their revenue and reduce user churn thanks to secure, always up to date credentials for returning customers. In this role, you will own the roadmap and business impact of one Stripe’s core business critical products. You will engage with key ecosystem partners such as card networks, partner with an experienced Engineering lead and collaborate with GTM teams to ensure Stripe’s card updater and tokenization solutions are defining the industry best-in-class standard.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the long-term vision and strategy for Stripe’s Card updater capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a holistic strategy for Stripe’s tokenization solutions to support our multiprocessor strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with users to deeply understand their needs, associated pain points and opportunitiesBuild and launch new capabilities that bring significant value to customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set priorities and execution roadmap for the team, innovate with your engineering team to identify novel opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Finance to maintain product P&amp;amp;L and identify opportunities for growth and improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other stakeholders across Stripe such as Data Science, Product Marketing, Payments Strategists and GTM teams to deliver high quality product experience to users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
